-- Pioneer Corp.’s Unifreight Purchase Delayed, Newsday Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-04-19T06:56:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-19/pioneer-corp-s-unifreight-purchase-delayed-newsday-reports.html
Pioneer Corp. (6773)  Africa Ltd.’s
decision to buy Unifreight Zimbabwe (Pvt) Ltd. has been delayed
by Zimbabwe’s Indigenization Ministry, Newsday said, citing
unidentified government officials and Pioneer Chairman Patrick Chingoka.  The deal has been approved by Zimbabwe’s Competition and
Tariff Commission, Harare-based Newsday said. Pioneer agreed to
pay $7.2 million for Unifreight, the newspaper said.  The transport company is in talks with the Indigenization
Ministry, said Newsday.  Pioneer owns freight and passenger transport companies in
Zimbabwe,  South Africa  and Botswana, Newsday said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
